    {
      "id": "RQ-0004",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Consolidate task materialization and slim task command helpers",
      "description": "The audit found that Ralph currently materializes new queue tasks through multiple overlapping paths. `commands/task/mod.rs` is carrying helper-surface, option, runner-resolution, request-reading, and field-diff responsibilities, while follow-up proposal application and task decomposition each allocate IDs, map dependencies, choose insertion points, stamp timestamps, and validate queue writes independently. This work should establish one canonical task-materialization path, reduce boundary drift in the task command surface, and keep follow-up/decomposition behavior aligned for IDs, dependency remapping, timestamps, insertion order, and validation.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "architecture",
        "queue",
        "task-builder",
        "refactor"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/task/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/task/decompose/",
        "crates/ralph/src/queue/operations/followups.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/queue/operations/",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop task",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop queue"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User request: \"use the comprehensive codebase audit skill and build tasks stemming from your findings\"",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/task/mod.rs:1-27 and 48-205 show the facade carrying helper docs, shared option types, runner-setting resolution, request parsing, and other cross-cutting task command responsibilities.",
        "crates/ralph/src/queue/operations/followups.rs:132-268 and 305-332 allocate follow-up IDs, materialize tasks, pick insertion points, and validate queue writes.",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/task/decompose/support.rs:83-189 and 364-389 separately allocate sequential IDs, materialize tasks, and choose queue insertion positions for decomposition output."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Map the current task-creation/write flows across task build/update, follow-up proposal apply, and decomposition so the canonical shared responsibilities are explicit.",
        "Refactor `commands/task/mod.rs` into a thin facade with focused companions for task types, runner-setting resolution, request IO, and field-diff helpers.",
        "Extract a shared queue-materialization layer that owns sequential ID allocation, dependency remapping, timestamp stamping, insertion strategy, and post-write validation.",
        "Cut follow-up application and decomposition over to that shared layer without changing their user-facing behavior or queue contract.",
        "Add or update focused tests that prove equivalent ordering, dependency wiring, and validation behavior across the consolidated paths.",
        "Run the relevant task/queue Rust test coverage and the canonical local gate needed to prove the refactor preserved behavior."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "use the comprehensive codebase audit skill and build tasks stemming from your findings",
      "created_at": "2026-04-25T16:45:55Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-25T16:45:55Z",
