    {
      "id": "RQ-0007",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Split oversized machine and release contract suites",
      "description": "The audit found contract-heavy test files that are carrying too many unrelated scenarios in a single place, which makes failures less local and pushes Ralph away from its own small-file guidance. `machine_contract_test.rs` is already a multi-surface end-to-end suite, and `pre_public_check_contracts_early.rs` has grown to nearly 1,000 lines. This task should reorganize those suites into directory-backed, behavior-grouped modules with shared helpers so contract coverage remains strong while maintenance and review costs come down.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "tests",
        "contracts",
        "maintainability",
        "release",
        "machine"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/release_integration_contract_test.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/release_integration_contract_test/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/test_support/",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop machine_contract_test",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop release_integration_contract_test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User request: \"use the comprehensive codebase audit skill and build tasks stemming from your findings\"",
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test.rs is 608 lines and already mixes queue, task mutation, recovery, parallel-status, and run-start contract coverage.",
        "crates/ralph/tests/release_integration_contract_test/pre_public_check_contracts_early.rs is 993 lines, well beyond the repo's preferred small-file target.",
        "The architecture audit called out `machine_contract_test.rs` as a monolithic contract suite that repeats repo bootstrap, JSON request assembly, command execution, and response assertions."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Map the current machine-contract and release-contract scenarios into coherent behavior groups with clear ownership boundaries.",
        "Split `machine_contract_test.rs` into a directory-backed suite organized by command family such as queue, task, recovery, workspace, and parallel/run contracts.",
        "Split the oversized pre-public-check contract coverage into smaller companion modules with shared fixture/setup helpers instead of one large file.",
        "Preserve existing assertions and helper reuse while improving failure locality and keeping the root test hubs thin.",
        "Run the affected contract test suites and the canonical local gate needed to ensure the reorganization did not drop coverage."
      ],
